{"serial": "52023", "department_serial": 51, "code": "CE3054", "class": "*", "name": {"en": "Introduction to Information Security", "ch": "資訊安全概論"}, "notice": {"en": "", "ch": ""}, "instructor": {"en": ["Yang,Hao-Tsung"], "ch": ["楊晧琮"]}, "credits": 3, "time_loc": [{"time": {"week": 2, "session": ["5", "6", "7"]}, "loc": {"building": "E6", "room": "A209"}}], "isRequired": false, "isFullSem": false, "MaxStu": 50, "department": {"ch": "資訊工程學系", "en": "Department of Computer Science and Elec. Engineering"}, "system": {"ch": "學士班", "en": "Undergraduate Programme"}, "language": {"ch": "英語", "en": "English"}, "card": {"ch": "部份使用", "en": "Optional"}, "assigned": 0, "selected": 37, "remark": {"ch": "", "en": ""}, "goal": {"ch": "This course will impart a technical and social understanding of how and why security and privacy matter, how to think adversarially, how (and how not) to design systems and products. Less attention will be paid to specific skills such as hacking, writing secure code, and security administration.\n\n(IMPORTANT!!) This course is an interactive course. There are a lot of class activity that students have to express their opinions, ask/ answer questions. Please do not enroll this course if you think you cannot handle it.", "en": "This course will impart a technical and social understanding of how and why security and privacy matter, how to think adversarially, how (and how not) to design systems and products. Less attention will be paid to specific skills such as hacking, writing secure code, and security administration.\n\n(IMPORTANT!!) This course is an interactive course. There are a lot of class activity that students have to express their opinions, ask/ answer questions. Please do not enroll this course if you think you cannot handle it."}, "outline": {"ch": "參考英文內容Topics include but limit to user authentication, cryptography, malware, behavioral economics in security, human factors in security, privacy and anonymity, adversarial modeling, and attack and defense in internet of things.\nWe start with basic cryptography theory to the state of the art. We will then explore these concepts by studying real-world systems and attacks, including retailer breaches, implantable medical devices, Bitcoin. We will also cover newly emerging issues such as attack in Deep learning, differential privacy, security and reliability in autonomous system and so on.", "en": "Topics include but limit to user authentication, cryptography, malware, behavioral economics in security, human factors in security, privacy and anonymity, adversarial modeling, and attack and defense in internet of things.\nWe start with basic cryptography theory to the state of the art. We will then explore these concepts by studying real-world systems and attacks, including retailer breaches, implantable medical devices, Bitcoin. We will also cover newly emerging issues such as attack in Deep learning, differential privacy, security and reliability in autonomous system and so on."}, "textbook": {"ch": "Handbook of Applied Cryptography by Alfred J. Menezes, Paul C. van Oorschot and Scott A. Vanstone (not necessary)", "en": "Handbook of Applied Cryptography by Alfred J. Menezes, Paul C. van Oorschot and Scott A. Vanstone (not necessary)"}, "selfCompiledRate": {"ch": "70%", "en": "70%"}, "instructMethod": {"ch": "講授", "en": ["Lecture"]}, "gradMethod": {"ch": "20％ Class activity\n20％ Group project\n20％ Midterm\n30％ Finals\n10％ Homework", "en": "20％ Class activity\n20％ Group project\n20％ Midterm\n30％ Finals\n10％ Homework"}, "officeHour": {"ch": "星期四 下午兩點到四點", "en": "Thu. 2:00 pm - 4:00 pm"}, "teachWeeks": {"ch": "16+2", "en": "16+2"}, "flexDiscription": {"ch": "自主學習、專題討論、並開放線上問答。", "en": "Study, self-learning, project discussion. Online meeting available."}, "domain": {"ch": "資安、網路、資料庫與系統研究群", "en": "資安、網路、資料庫與系統研究群"}, "map": {"ch": [{"competencies": "數理邏輯能力", "rating": "(4)高", "assesments": ["紙筆測驗/會考", "作業練習", "口頭報告/口試", "專題研究報告(書面)", "實作/實驗", "出席/課堂表現", "學習檔案評量